### `training/` (the loop)

| File / subdir | What |
|---|---|
| `mod.rs` | the training loop itself (`train(...)`) |
| `features/` | optional features: `masked_loss`, `timestep_bias`, `caption_dropout`, `caption_aug`, `image_aug`, `tread`, `slider`, `multi_backend`, `ema_advanced`, `noise_modifiers`, `lr_schedule`, `loss_weight`, `validation`, `disk_check`, `health`, `sample_library`, `webhook`, `asymflow_loss` |
| `training_features/` | unified config types: `optimizers`, `sampler`, `timestep_dist`, `ema` (consolidated 2026-05-10 across all trainers) |
| `block_offload.rs` | per-layer weight streaming for large models on 24 GB |
| `training_offload.rs` / `offload.rs` | activation + optimizer-state offload |
| `checkpoint.rs` | save/resume |
| `board.rs` | metrics → SQLite (`board.db`, `scalars` table) — trainers are silent on stdout without `RUST_LOG=info` |
| `save_direct.rs` | LoRA save (PEFT/ai-toolkit format, all trainers, by design) |
| `ema.rs` | parameter EMA |
| `grad_coverage.rs` | grad-flow assertions, complements `flame_core::diagnostics::assert_grad_flow` |
| `schedule.rs` | learning-rate schedules |
| `progress.rs` / `logging.rs` | logs and tqdm-like progress |

### `encoders/`

Every text + VAE encoder used by any trainer lives here. Adding a new model
means adding its tokenizer/encoder here OR reusing one (e.g. T5-XXL is shared
across multiple). VAEs are first-class — encode happens in `prepare_*`, decode
in `sample_*`.

### `sampler/`

Per-model sampling code used by `sample_*` binaries and mid-training preview.
Separate from `flame-core`'s sampling primitives — these wire model + scheduler
+ VAE end-to-end.

## 3. Where to start for common tasks

| Task | Start here |
|---|---|
| Add a new trainer | `crates/eridiffusion-core/src/models/<name>.rs` + a `pipeline/` impl + `crates/eridiffusion-cli/src/bin/train_<name>.rs` + a flat `configs/<name>.json` |
| Debug a training run | `RUST_LOG=info` (else silent stdout), then `board.db` scalars |
| Grad-flow regression | `FLAME_ASSERT_GRAD_FLOW=1` + `crate::training::grad_coverage` |
| OOM on 24 GB | `training/block_offload.rs` (per-layer streaming) + `training/training_offload.rs` (activations) |
| Parity vs PyTorch trainer | per-model `bin/parity_<model>_*.rs` + `flame_core::parity::ParityHarness` |
| Dataset prep OOM (~75 samples) | confirm `FLAME_ALLOC_POOL=0` set at `main()` start in the `prepare_*` bin |
| Pre-fix Klein/ERNIE/Flux/SDXL/Z-Image LoRAs are invalid | HWC→CHW transpose bug fixed 2026-05-05 in all `prepare_*.rs`; pre-fix latents were std≈0.85 not ≈0.96 |
| LoRA save format | `training/save_direct.rs` writes PEFT/ai-toolkit (intentional, not a bug) |
| Convert LoRA between formats | `bin/convert_zimage_lora.rs` is the template |
| Klein step-2 crash | resolved 2026-05-13: trainer auto-disables `FLAME_ALLOC_POOL` (mirrors `prepare_klein:194`) |

## 4. Configs

`configs/*.json` — flat directory of per-run configs (e.g. `klein9b_alina.json`,
`eri2_chroma_lora.json`, `asymflux2_klein_lora.json`). NO per-model subdirs.
Per-model flags surface here that aren't in code defaults;
**grep the trainer + config in tandem when porting settings between models.**

## 5. Reference / parity material

`reference/` (165k lines) is read-only vendored Python — OneTrainer, ai-toolkit,
and per-model official training scripts. Used for:
- Cross-checking forward pass when a parity test diverges
- Generating per-layer GPU-streaming parity captures
- Confirming optimizer / scheduler semantics

**Never edit `reference/`. Never `cargo`-include it. Never CPU-stream a parity
reference — see CONTEXT.md / project memory: BF16 CPU vs CUDA diverge at cos=0.5
per layer.**

## 6. Gotchas (project-wide invariants)

- **`flame-core` is the producer.** When N trainers share a bug, fix flame-core,
  not N trainer workarounds. `.contiguous()` sprinkles are stopgaps only.
- **Pure-Rust runtime.** Python is a dev tool (parity refs, debug scripts).
  Never ship Python.
- **Z-Image = base bf16, not turbo.** Turbo is separately distilled; sampling
  expectations differ.
- **Klein 9B is the proving ground after Phase 5d.** Do not propose 4B fallback
  when 9B hits friction.
- **Wan2.2 is the quant exception.** FP8 / AdamW8bit allowed on Wan only —
  14B+14B doesn't fit FP16 on 24 GB. No-quant rule applies to Z-Image.
- **LyCORIS LoKr `factor=N` is factored W2.** For full-W2 LoKr use
  `--rank 1000 --lora-alpha 1000`; `--rank N --lokr-factor N` gives a dead
  `w2_b=0` leaf.
- **OneTrainer doesn't use fused kernels.** Don't blame fusion for trainer-level
  slowness — investigate sync patterns first.
- **LyCORIS overhead ≈ +2.1 s/step on zimage rank=8.** Benchmark against plain
  `--algo lora` for apples-to-apples flame-core perf.
- **`assert_grad_flow` checks step-1, not step-0.** Step 0 has expected
  uninitialized-leaf fires; step 1 is the real signal.

